import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import { getDashboardStats, getScrapingJobs } from '../utils/api'; function Dashboard() { const [stats, setStats] = useState({}); const [jobs, setJobs] = useState([]); useEffect(() => { loadData(); }, []); const loadData = async () => { try { const [statsRes, jobsRes] = await Promise.all([ getDashboardStats(), getScrapingJobs() ]); setStats(statsRes.data); setJobs(jobsRes.data.slice(0, 5)); // Show last 5 jobs } catch (error) { console.error('Error loading dashboard data:', error); } }; return (

Dashboard

{/* Stats Cards */}
J
Total Jobs
{stats.totalJobs || 0}
P
Total Products
{stats.totalProducts || 0}
C
Completed Jobs
{stats.completedJobs || 0}
%
Success Rate
{Math.round(stats.successRate || 0)}%
{/* Recent Jobs */}

Recent Jobs

    {jobs.map((job) => (

  • {job.name}

    {job.status}

    {job.scrapedProducts || 0} products

    Website: {job.website}

    {new Date(job.createdAt).toLocaleDateString()}

    • ))}
); } export default Dashboard;
